        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-06-04T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-06-04T17:00:00-05:00" n="389" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d389">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894A.02/6–249: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul at Taipei</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Edgar</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-06-04T18:00:00-04:00">June 4, 1949—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>121. Fol is Cantel 522 June 2 to Dept: [Here follows text of Cantel 522, <ref target="#pg_344">page 344</ref>.]</p>
                <p>ECA Wash, Lapham, and Dept agree above recommendation and that approach Chen
                    should be made by Craig in sense last para reftel. Please inform Craig. Dept is
                    authorizing Clark approach S. Y. Liu as suggested.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
